alert.note: Alert for Citrus; Levy (Florida) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.headline: Flood Warning issued September 29 at 12:33AM EDT until further notice by NWS Tampa Bay
info.description: ...The Flood Warning continues for the following rivers in Florida... Withlacoochee At US 41 Dunnellon affecting Levy and Citrus Counties. For the Withlacoochee...including US 41 Dunnellon...Minor flooding is forecast. ...FLOOD WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM FRIDAY AFTERNOON UNTIL FURTHER NOTICE... * WHAT...Minor flooding is forecast. * WHERE...Withlacoochee At US 41 Dunnellon. * WHEN...From Friday afternoon until further notice. * IMPACTS...At 29.0 feet, Docks and boat ramps flood. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 11:45 PM EDT Wednesday the stage was 27.7 feet. - Forecast...The river is expected to rise above flood stage on Saturday rising to 29.3 feet on Monday. Additional rises are possible thereafter. - Flood stage is 29.0 feet. - Flood History...This crest compares to a previous crest of 29.3 feet on 10/12/1995. - https://www.weather.gov/safety/flood && Fld Observed Forecasts (2 am EDT) Location Stg Stg Day/Time Fri Sat Sun Mon Tue Withlacoochee US 41 Dunnello 29.0 27.7 Wed 11 pm 28.4 28.9 29.1 29.2 MSG &&
info.instruction: Be especially cautious at night when it is harder to recognize the dangers of flooding. Turn around, don`t drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood deaths occur in vehicles. Additional information is available at www.weather.gov. The next statement will be issued as warranted.
